About this item

  • Multi-Functional Sports Tracking & Health Monitoring: Supports over 100 sports modes including running, cycling, swimming, and more. Real-time tracking helps you reach your fitness goals. Built-in high-precision sensors monitor heart rate and blood oxygen levels, providing 24/7 health monitoring to keep your well-being at its best.
  • Special Care Features for Women: Thoughtfully designed with women's health in mind, this smartwatch can track and predict menstrual cycles, keeping you informed about your body’s changes. Combined with various health data, it provides accurate health advice, offering comfort and care to female users.
  • Smart Notifications & Bluetooth Calling: Stay connected on the go with smart notifications and Bluetooth calling. Sync your smartwatch with your phone to receive call, SMS, and app notifications directly on your wrist. The built-in Bluetooth call feature allows you to answer calls without needing to reach for your phone.
  • Variety of Watch Faces & Customization Options: With over 400 watch faces to choose from and the option to create custom designs, you can personalize your smartwatch to match your style. The sleek design and multiple color options make this smartwatch not just a functional device but also a fashion statement.
  • Long-Lasting Battery & Smart Reminders: Enjoy up to one week of battery life, reducing the need for frequent charging. The smartwatch also features smart reminders for alarms, sedentary alerts, hydration reminders, and medication alerts, helping you manage your daily routine and maintain a healthy lifestyle.

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Amazon Customer
      5 out of 5 stars
      A Great Smart Watch!
      This is a really nice watch for a very reasonable price. Before writing this review I played around with it for five days and tried out just about every function it has. They all work. All you need to do is give it all the permissions that it requests. There’s a page in the app that you download on your phone that requests permissions. I was initially concerned that allowing it to constantly run in the background of my phone would drain my battery, and the app said that was a possibiity, but I noticed no difference in my phone’s battery function. In fact, it used only 6% of the battery.Setting it up the first time was a little confusing. There was one screen that had a button that should have taken me to my phone’s settings and it didn’t work. I tapped the “ignore” button to get out of the screen and went to settings myself. The problem is that every phone’s settings are different. I have a Samsung S23. My husband has a Samsung S24. The settings are completely different. So it’s really impossible to provide instructions that will be accurate on every phone. One last tip is that when you get to the point where you’re setting up your profile (gender, height, weight, etc) the button you need to tap to proceed to the next screen is in the center at the bottom of the screen. It’s very light. If you don’t know it’s there, you won’t see it. You are also given the option to set it up for metric or imperial measurements. Once you get through the initial setup, everything works great. Like I said in the first paragraph, just give it all the permissions it wants and it will work great for you.Now the fun stuff. I guess I’ll start with the appearance. It came in a very attractive box which would make for a very nice Christmas gift. The watch has 440 watch faces! I took screenshots from the app of some of them to give you an idea of what’s available. With that many watch faces you have to be able to find something you like. You can also customize watch faces if you like. It comes with two different styles of watchband. Both are silicone, one has a normal watchband buckle and the other allows you to tuck the excess band between the watchband and your arm. The band size is 20mm so if you want to purchase different watchbands you can.Regarding the functionality, first I want to remind you that it’s connected to your phone via bluetooth so you have to keep your phone near your watch, otherwise the connection will be broken. If that happens, the watch vibrates and the dial displays a message indicating that you’ve lost the connection. As soon as you are back within range of your phone it automatically reconnects. I found that notification feature to be useful in preventing me from leaving my house without my phone. I’ve done that a few times in the past and it’s very inconvenient. This watch will make sure you don’t do that. The watch has so many functions that there’s no way I can describe, or even list, all of them. I took a lot of pictures, though, so you can see for yourself what functions are available and what they look like on the watch face and your phone. I will discuss a few, though.You can set it up to receive all your text messages as well as notifications from social media apps like FB, Messenger, WhatsApp, Nextdoor and more. Other apps you can receive notifications from include Instagram, YouTube, Gmail, Snapchat, X and Pinterest. That list is probably not all inclusive. I tested the text message function as well as the four social media apps I just mentioned and the watch did not miss a single notification. 100% accuracy for five days! You can also answer your phone using the watch. I had my husband call me and I was able to answer the phone and speak to him through the watch while my phone was in my pocket. He said my voice came across crystal clear! I was also able to make phone calls using the watch. I didn’t import my contacts because I have a lot of them. I just dialed my husband because I know his number by heart. The speaker on the watch works very well.I set seven different alarms just to test how many it would allow me to set and I can safely say you can set at least seven to go off every day. I got bored after that and didn’t try to set up anymore alarms. I doubt anyone would need to set up more. The alarm goes off whether you are wearing the watch or charging it and it’s loud enough for you to hear. It’s a really nice function.The sleep monitoring function is my favorite. It shows on the watch and your phone. I’ve included photos of both. It also records your heart rate, blood oxygen record, stress record, emotion record, steps, calories burned and kilometers covered. It can be personalized to record for may different kinds of exercises including but not limited to pushups, situps, gymnastics, tennis, walking and running. It also provides weather reports as well as two different games.Like any new device you’ll have to play around with it to get used to it and to discover all the functionality it has to offer. You can swipe up, down, right and left to get to different menus.I’m very happy with this watch. It has so much more functionality that watches that cost much more and it’s even waterproof. You can’t go wrong with this watch. I really think you’ll love it.
